            "title": "### 2. **Key Tourist Places in Karnataka",
            "content": [
                {
                    "subtitle": "A. Historical and Heritage Sites",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "text": "**Hampi (UNESCO World Heritage Site):**"
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Famous for the ancient ruins of Vijayanagara Empire."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Highlights: Virupaksha Temple, Vittala Temple, Stone Chariot."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "A popular destination for history buffs and photography enthusiasts."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "**Badami:**"
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Known for rock-cut temples and historical fortifications."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "A significant Chalukya architectural site."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "**Bijapur (Vijayapura):**"
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Famous for its Islamic architecture."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Key attractions: Gol Gumbaz, Ibrahim Roza, and Bijapur Fort."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "**Mysore:**"
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "The city is famous for Mysore Palace, Chamundeshwari Temple, and the Dussehra festival."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Known for silk, sandalwood, and its royal history."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "**Srirangapatna:**"
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Historical town near Mysore, associated with Tipu Sultan."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Important sites: Tipu Sultan\u2019s Summer Palace, Ranganathaswamy Temple, and the Dariya Daulat Bagh."
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "subtitle": "B. Natural Attractions and Scenic Spots",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "text": "**Coorg (Kodagu):**"
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Known for its coffee plantations, waterfalls, and misty hills."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Popular spots: Abbey Falls, Dubare Elephant Camp, Raja\u2019s Seat."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "**Chikmagalur:**"
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Famous for coffee estates and scenic hills."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Key locations: Mullayanagiri, Baba Budangiri, and Hebbe Falls."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "**Agumbe:**"
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Known as the \"Cherrapunji of the South\" for its monsoon rains."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Famous for sunsets and rich biodiversity."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "The Agumbe Rainforest Research Station (ARRS) is located here."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "**Kabini:**"
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Popular for wildlife safari and the Kabini River."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Wildlife enthusiasts can explore Nagarhole National Park."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "**Gokarna:**"
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Known for pristine beaches like Om Beach and Kudle Beach."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "A more peaceful alternative to Goa."
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "subtitle": "C. Beaches and Coastal Destinations",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "text": "**Udupi:**"
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Famous for its temples, beaches, and coastal cuisine."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Malpe Beach is popular for water sports."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "**Karwar:**"
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Known for its serene beaches and the peaceful atmosphere."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Rabindranath Tagore Beach and Devbagh Beach are major attractions."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "**Kundapur:**"
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Offers beautiful, less crowded beaches like Kodi Beach."
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "subtitle": "D. Wildlife and Nature Reserves",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "text": "**Bandipur National Park:**"
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "A major wildlife sanctuary in Karnataka, home to tigers, elephants, and a variety of flora and fauna."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "**Nagarhole National Park:**"
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Known for its rich biodiversity and picturesque landscapes."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "**Bhadra Wildlife Sanctuary:**"
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Home to tigers, leopards, and other wildlife."
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Located in the Western Ghats."
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
